BT
/F1 11 Tf
50 750 Td
12 TL
(PowerFlex 525 AC Drive) Tj
T*
(Fault Code Reference Manual) Tj
T*
(Rockwell Automation / Allen-Bradley) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SECTION 1: FAULT CODES) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(F004 UnderVoltage) Tj
T*
(Description: DC bus voltage fell below minimum level.) Tj
T*
(Possible Causes:) Tj
T*
(  - Low incoming line voltage) Tj
T*
(  - Loose input power connections) Tj
T*
(  - Power line disturbance or momentary power loss) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Corrective Actions:) Tj
T*
(  1. Check incoming line voltage at the drive input terminals.) Tj
T*
(     Verify voltage is within drive rating \(480VAC +/-10%\).) Tj
T*
(  2. Inspect input power connections for loose terminals or corrosion.) Tj
T*
(  3. Check for other loads on the same power circuit causing voltage sag.) Tj
T*
(  4. Verify DC bus voltage using a multimeter on the DC+ and DC- terminals.) Tj
T*
(  5. If voltage dips are momentary, consider adding a line reactor or UPS.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(F005 OverVoltage) Tj
T*
(Description: DC bus voltage exceeded maximum level.) Tj
T*
(Possible Causes:) Tj
T*
(  - High incoming line voltage) Tj
T*
(  - Regenerative energy from decelerating load) Tj
T*
(  - Deceleration rate set too fast) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Corrective Actions:) Tj
T*
(  1. Check incoming line voltage - must not exceed drive maximum rating.) Tj
T*
(  2. Increase deceleration time \(Parameter A440\).) Tj
T*
(  3. Install a dynamic braking resistor if load is regenerative.) Tj
T*
(  4. Verify DC bus voltage is within normal operating range \(650-700VDC for 480V) Tj
T*
(\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SECTION 2: SAFETY WARNINGS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(WARNING: LOCKOUT/TAGOUT REQUIRED) Tj
T*
(Before performing any maintenance on this drive:) Tj
T*
(  - Disconnect and lockout all power sources per LOTO procedures.) Tj
T*
(  - Wait 5 minutes after power removal before opening enclosure.) Tj
T*
(  - Verify zero voltage with a calibrated meter before touching internal parts.) Tj
T*
(  - Follow site lockout/tagout policy and OSHA 1910.147 requirements.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SECTION 3: MAINTENANCE INTERVALS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Monthly:) Tj
T*
(  - Inspect drive cooling vents for blockage) Tj
T*
(  - Check ambient temperature \(must be below 50 deg C\)) Tj
T*
(  - Verify fan operation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Annual:) Tj
T*
(  - Clean heat sink fins with compressed air \(drive de-energized, LOTO applied\)) Tj
T*
(  - Inspect power connections for torque and corrosion) Tj
T*
(  - Test ESTOP function) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SECTION 4: SPECIFICATIONS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Drive model: 25B-D010N104) Tj
T*
(Input: 480VAC 3-Phase 50/60 Hz) Tj
T*
(Output: 0-480VAC 3-Phase) Tj
T*
(HP Rating: 5 HP \(3.7 kW\)) Tj
T*
(DC Bus Nominal: 675 VDC) Tj
T*
(Overload: 150% for 60 seconds) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET

endstream
